About this app

The Sensartics Farm Monitor app allows farmers to remotely monitor and manage their farms using a network of sensors. The app would likely provide features like:

Real-time sensor data: View live data from various sensors deployed around the farm, including soil moisture, temperature, humidity, light levels, and nutrient content.
Sensor alerts: Set up alerts to be notified when sensor readings fall outside of desired ranges, indicating potential issues like irrigation problems or nutrient deficiencies.
Data visualization: View historical sensor data in graphs and charts to track trends and make informed decisions about farm management.
